  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\nFrom the point of view of the Design System, the current implementation of notification dots over tabs use a hardcoded background color to create the illusion of a cutout. This can be considered a bug, because it never worked with blurred backgrounds.\r\n\r\n### Expected solution\r\n\r\nUse an actual cutout on the corner of the tab. Unfortunately in ReactNative the solution requires using an SVG because there's no support for the CSS `clip-path` property.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/46027/214557691-18e04d06-76d9-4d56-85ae-d7712f8be8ee.png\" width=\"600\" />\r\n\r\n### References\r\n\r\nhttps://www.figma.com/file/WQZcp6S0EnzxdTL4taoKDv/Design-System?node-id=57%3A13215&t=mzgyr5OSrRuJKUhH-0",
